column34:
Implement in-app release notes - English ONLY and {color:#DE350B}*using Apple Native implementation of Markdown*{color}

*Overview*

Implement the new feature to show available Firmware release notes to the user. Extend the already-used query {{ProductDetailsById}} with the following inside {{{}availableProductSoftware{}}}, like so:
{code:java}
query ProductDetailsById($hardwareProductId: ID!, $language: String!) {
  hardwareProduct(id: $hardwareProductId) {
    availableProductSoftware {
      releaseNotes(language: $language) {
        header
        body
      }
    }
  }
}
{code}
Playground link: [https://api.silica-prod01.io.lens.poly.com/graphql?%2BAYKGeSBMUAs8LQmBA8yAA]

*Note*

By extending {{ProductDetailsById}} with {{{}releaseNotes(language: $language){}}}, we will be able to obtain localized release notes for the latest Firmware version that our app provides over-the-air device firmware update.

*Implementation details*

Most of the headsets that our app supports currently do not provide {{releaseNotes}} data, so as a workaround for the development purpose, pid {color:#172b4d}*{{Studio X30}}*{color} can be used.

If the device release notes data is not available for the available Firmware version, present an alert to the user, informing him about the data unavailability. Text copy: "Information about this update isn’t available at the moment. Please check back later."

Currently, localization does return release notes text in English only, regardless of what language parameter is used.

⭐ *FIGMA DESIGN* ⭐ [https://www.figma.com/design/kVruq94TvQDlPCELGmJcs5/Studio-Mobile-Spec?node-id=3635-24985&t=cS4F4XSnK29oOwVA-4]

!Screenshot 2025-06-25 at 11.47.06.png|width=100%!

