column1636:
22/Jan/25 9:34 PM;carrianne.minick@hp.com;[~seema.nikam@hp.com] I spoke with [~jason.knopsnyder@hp.com] about battery reporting and the headset should report battery level via Deckard events. Due to differences in battery capacities across headsets, sometimes a headset with 33% battery will be Low and other times it may be Medium. Lens should be able to take the battery information reported from the headset and then use the appropriate icon for battery High, Medium, Low. 

Here is a link to a Jira comment related to the implementation of battery status reporting [HSFWCH-7397|https://hp-jira.external.hp.com/browse/HSFWCH-7397?focusedId=13514664&amp;page=com.atlassian.jira.plugin.system.issuetabpanels%3Acomment-tabpanel#comment-13514664]

 ;;;

