column34:
*As an* end-user of the Falcon headset, 
*I want* the app to display the correct headset image based on the cushion type (On-Ear or Over-Ear), 
*So that* I can see an accurate representation of my Falcon headset in the Lens Mobile app
h2. Dependencies
 - *HEADSET* - Engineers needs Falcon units
 - *FW* - The firmware will implement the Deckard event to detect and inform about cushion type used on the device.
 - *CLOUD* - Tagged images from Cloud (On-Ear or Over-Ear)

h2. Acceptance Criteria
h3. Rule-based Acceptance Criteria
 - The Lens app displays the correct headset image based on the detected cushion type (On-Ear or Over-Ear)
 - The Lens app gets the images from the Cloud (tagged)
 - The Lens app displays last detected cushion and persists the information if the headset is not connected

h3. Scenario-oriented Accepance Criteria
h4. Main Scenario: Detect Falcon Headset Cushion Type on Connection

1. {color:#4c9aff}*Given*{color} the Falcon headset with *on-ear* cushions is connected via bluetooth to a mobile device (iPhone and Android smartphone),
2. {color:#ffab00}*When*{color} the user opens the Lens Mobile app,
3. {color:#ff8b00}*Then*{color} the Lens app displays an image of the Falcon headset with *on-ear* cushions
4. {color:#ffab00}*When*{color} the user changes the cushions to *over-ear*
5. {color:#ff8b00}*Then*{color} the Falcon headset sends an event out (FW) to the Lens Mobile app (Deckard)
*And* the Lens app updates the display to show the Falcon headset with *over-ear* cushions.
6. {color:#ffab00}*When*{color} the user disconnects the Flacon Headset (Bluetooth)
*And* it shows disconnected in the Lens Mobile app
7. {color:#ff8b00}*Then*{color} the Lens Mobile app shows Falcon headset with last cushion configuration image (retrieved from Lens Cloud)

h2. [Cloud GraphQL Dev|https://api.silica-dev01.glass.plthab.com/graphql?explorerURLState=N4IgJg9gxgrgtgUwHYBcQC4QEcYIE4CeABABICGeYA7hQgAp4RgxQoAUAJABYXW0NMWKAJJh0RYQBEAhAEoiwADp5FSIkR6Uaeeo2as2ASzFFuvbbsGtR8pSrXqix5asdEkZRC4fqADnqFhODIAcwQAZwVvN3UEMDDIu1cY9SQmBCj7FLcUUMTo7LdnLMLHAGsEAgLSogA3MgAbXGrS5BRDFAIAFTIAIwaEADlPBBbCto6CACUEBrJ2iCRRMZiAXxX1dZK3LeTNgt2kVZAAGhB6vEM%2BgfCMECSHRRBNPh0BfREwJ-EnqF6AMye3mOqyAA] 

h3. Query

{code:json}
query HardwareProduct($hardwareProductId: ID!) {
  hardwareProduct(id: $hardwareProductId) {
    id
    name
    productImages {
      edges {
        node {
          tags {
            id
            key
            value
            entityTableName
            entityRelationId
          }
        }
      }
    }
  }
}
{code}

h2. Variables

{code:json}
{
  "hardwareProductId": "cbf"
}
{code}

h3. Result

{code:json}
{
  "data": {
    "hardwareProduct": {
      "id": "cbf",
      "name": "HP Poly Focus 620",
      "productImages": {
        "edges": [
          {
            "node": {
              "tags": []
            }
          },
          {
            "node": {
              "tags": [
                {
                  "id": "277014c4-c878-44bd-9e55-3738b1fc951e",
                  "key": "EAR_CUSHION_TYPE",
                  "value": "onear",
                  "entityTableName": "hardware_model_image",
                  "entityRelationId": "31f7ba2a-61b1-4740-9940-dc58e0ace39b"
                }
              ]
            }
          },
          {
            "node": {
              "tags": [
                {
                  "id": "65aee920-fbad-4551-bca9-eb492fd7db89",
                  "key": "EAR_CUSHION_TYPE",
                  "value": "overear",
                  "entityTableName": "hardware_model_image",
                  "entityRelationId": "4788c2e9-2c48-48a1-9e59-3f9990af63c1"
                }
              ]
            }
          }
        ]
      }
    }
  }
}
{code}


h1. ---- ORIGINAL DESCRIPTION ----

As an end-user of the headset, I should see the proper image displayed in the app, based on the Falcon headset type, On Ear or Over the Ear.

The firmware will provide the Deckard command.

Acceptance criteria:
Display a proper image of the headset in the app.

