column1625:
26/Mar/25 5:49 PM;sebastian.hat-poly@hp.com;I’ve identified some challenges related to this task. Currently, the Quick Start Guide is managed separately for iOS and Android, with certain changes already applied independently on both platforms.

 

We should investigate whether our UI implementations can support a unified JSON structure. While using separate JSON files for each platform might offer greater flexibility for the iOS and Android teams, it could also introduce additional overhead for cloud-side management—especially if responsibilities shift between teams.

 

On the other hand, adopting a shared JSON would require every change to be coordinated and approved by all stakeholders, potentially slowing down the implementation process.;;;

column1626:
31/Mar/25 11:46 AM;sebastian.hat-poly@hp.com;Based on the team’s discussion, we recommend closing this ticket. The ticket is quite outdated, and we have not received any recent confirmation from the cloud team on whether replacing local JSON files and assets with cloud-provided versions is still relevant.

Additionally, due to existing differences between the iOS and Android JSON implementations, unifying them at this stage would require significantly more effort.

cc: [~geeta.wyporek@hp.com] , [~joel.maranhao@hp.com] , [~ujjaval.gupta@hp.com] ;;;

column1623:
17/Apr/25 10:50 AM;julia.walter@hp.com;I reviewed the findings and tested the app with external keyboard and VoiceOver. Some of the original issues are still present, but the ticket is quite outdated. Some broader problems exist now too, for example the menu button isn't reachable via keyboard or screen reader. 
A new accessibility review might be helpful before we move forward.

CC [~joel.maranhao@hp.com], [~michal.szatkowski@hp.com];;;

